.content.
  Not all Asian or Asian American males are typecasted
  as the kung-fu master; that role requires a certain
  character and physique. The other Asian men 
  who have graced US media did so through another
  role: the clown, the jester, the butt of the joke.
  Remember <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_hung">
  William Hung</a>? Despite his terrible performance
  on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_Idol">
  American Idol</a>, his appearance on the show 
  garnered him international stardom and even a record
  deal. He had no talent (he said so himself), 
  fit the look of a stereotypical nerdy
  Asian, and spoke with a noticeable accent.
  Many have attributed his fame to mockery and 
  white hegemonic propagation of entrenched
  Asian sterotypes. In other words, he stood 
  in front of US media as a joke. 
